CM GUI -> Clusters -> -> Dynamic Resource Pool Configuration
For “Resources Pools” Tab, find total number of vcores and memory in the context. In cluster, it is 288 vcores and 288G memory total.
Calculate the number. 50% of total and memory are 144 vcores / 144 Gib memory
Edit “root -> default” pool and modify “Virtual Cores Max” & “Virtual Core Min”
If policy has multiple configuration set, modify all of them. For example, in Preprod default pool, you will see “default”, “day”, “night”, weekends” for different time slots.
Save and refresh configuration.
